</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="169" pageNumber="931" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="169.[132,1340,287,794]" pageId="169" pageNumber="931">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[134,491,524,557]" pageId="169" pageNumber="931">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Endangered on The IUCN Red List. The Flatheaded 
<taxonomicName box="[248,337,563,596]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="169" pageNumber="931" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
has an extremely restricted distribution, there are less than 250 mature individuals, and the population is probably declining because of wood exploitation and other disturbances in land use. Discovery of a new population near the known distribution in 2005 indicates it is not extinct, as it was once supposed to be.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
